Verdin's breakfast includes eggs, avocado, and salmon, providing sustained energy and supporting overall well-being.
title: Longevity scientist who reversed his age by 15 years shares go-to breakfast

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: The Supreme Court has agreed to hear a petition from Ashoka University professor Ali Khan Mahmudabad, arrested by Haryana Police for his remarks on Operation Sindoor. CJI B R Gavai's bench will hear the matter on May 20 or 21. Mahmudabad's arrest, following a BJP Yuva Morcha leader's complaint, has sparked concern over free expression within the academic community.
title: SC agrees to hear Ashoka Univ prof's PIL against arrest for remarks on Op Sindoor

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack and Operation Sindoor, a senior Trinamool Congress leader emphasized that foreign policy is the Union government's exclusive domain. While pledging support to protect the nation, the leader's statement came as India prepares to dispatch all-party delegations to key partner countries to reinforce its stance against terrorism.
title: 'TMC MP Yusuf Pathan opts out of all-party delegation on Op Sindoor'

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Following heightened tensions and Operation Sindoor, Pakistan launched missile and drone attacks targeting Indian cities. The Indian Army, anticipating the threat, successfully intercepted these attacks, particularly safeguarding the Golden Temple from potential destruction. Modern air defence systems, including the indigenous AKASH missile system, played a crucial role in thwarting Pakistan's nefarious designs.
title: Watch: Army shows how India’s air defence foiled Pak bid to strike Golden Temple

author: TNN
description: In a significant operation, the Uttar Pradesh Anti-Terrorist Squad (ATS) apprehended Shehzad Wahab, a Rampur-based trader, for allegedly spying for Pakistan under the guise of cross-border smuggling. Wahab, who frequently visited Pakistan, is accused of sharing sensitive information with the ISI, facilitating financial transactions, and recruiting individuals for espionage.
title: Who is Shehzad Wahab? UP trader-turned Pak spy under guise of crossborder trade

author: AVIJIT GHOSH
title: Why a clash of two Rajesh Khanna superhits left Mahesh Bhatt crying

author: HAMSAVENI N
description: Residents of Sai Layout in Bengaluru's Horamavu are grappling with severe waterlogging and flooding, even before the monsoon season. Pre-monsoon rains submerged the area, leaving homes flooded and residents without access to clean water. The BBMP is working on temporary solutions like pumping water while a long-term project to restore the stormwater drain's width is underway with railway authorities.
title: Bengaluru flooded again, residents blame official apathy, dread monsoon arrival

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: In Borno, Nigeria, a devastating attack by Boko Haram's JAS faction resulted in at least 57 deaths and over 70 missing from two villages, with victims accused of being informants for ISWAP.
title: Deadly Boko Haram attack kills 57, leaves 70 missing in Nigeria's villages

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Tom Cruise's Mission: Impossible – The Final Reckoning had a great start in India. The film earned Rs 33 crore in two days. It became the highest-grossing Hollywood film opening of 2025. The movie surpassed Final Destination Bloodlines and Thunderbolts. Strong bookings and Cruise's popularity helped. The film's success gave a boost to the Indian box office.
title: Know the 'Mission: Impossible – The Final Reckoning' box office collection

description: Stock market today: Indian equity benchmark indices, Nifty50 and BSE Sensex, opened in red on Monday. While Nifty50 was near 25,000, BSE Sensex was above 82,200.
title: Nifty50 near 25,000; BSE Sensex opens over 100 points down

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: According to doctors, taking vitamin D supplements might be a simple, safe, and cost-effective way to reduce fibroid risk and control their growth. Some clinical studies have shown that women who took vitamin D supplements experienced smaller fibroid sizes and slower tumor growth even as they age, thus proving the correlation between the two. However more clinical trials are needed to confirm the same
title: Vitamin D deficiency and fibroids: Why this is more harmful than we think

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Kuldeep Yadav's frustration boiled over after an umpire's call denied him an early wicket against Gujarat Titans. Sai Sudharsan, the beneficiary of the call, went on to score a century, leading the Titans to a dominant 10-wicket victory over Delhi Capitals.
title: Watch: Kuldeep Yadav loses cool, confronts umpire during DC vs GT match

author: ASSEEM SHAIKH
description: A year has passed since a 17-year-old's Porsche crash in Pune claimed the lives of two tech professionals, Ashwini Koshta and Anish Awadhia. The Juvenile Justice Board is yet to decide whether to try him as an adult, facing delays due to adjournments and quorum issues.
title: Pune Porsche crash: Adult or juvenile? One year on, no decision yet on teen driver

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Amid growing international pressure, Israel will allow a "basic amount" of food into Gaza, following warnings of a hunger crisis. This decision coincides with intensified military operations and ongoing ceasefire talks with Hamas in Qatar. Negotiations aim for hostage release and disarmament of Gaza, but disagreements persist over ceasefire terms.
title: After two months of aid blockade, Israel to allow 'basic amount' of food into Gaza

author: ANJALI SINGH
description: Ashoka University professor Ali Khan Mahmudabad was arrested following complaints about his comments on 'Operation Sindoor'. Haryana State Women’s Commission chairperson Renu Bhatia and BJP Yuva Morcha's Yogesh Jatheri filed separate FIRs, alleging threats to national integrity and promoting enmity. The faculty association has condemned the arrest as harassment, citing Mahmudabad's commitment to communal harmony.
title: Ashoka University professor held for ‘endangering unity’ over post on Op Sindoor

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Stock market recommendations: Motilal Oswal Financial Services recommends Bharti Airtel and Varun Beverages as top stock picks for the week starting May 19, 2025. They favor Bharti Airtel's premiumization and expect significant free cash flow generation. Varun Beverages delivered strong revenue growth and is expected to capitalize on India's beverage market.
title: Buy or sell: Top stock recommendations for today

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Punjab Kings defeated Rajasthan Royals by 10 runs, fueled by explosive half-centuries from Nehal Wadhera and Shashank Singh, alongside Harpreet Brar's crucial three-wicket haul. Despite a strong start from RR's openers and a fifty from Dhruv Jurel, they fell short. Arshdeep Singh shared a light moment with Jaiswal after the match.
title: 'Dhaga khol diya bey': Yashasvi-Arshdeep's on-field drama

author: MANVIR SAINI
description: Security agencies arrested YouTuber Jyoti Malhotra and three others for allegedly spying for Pakistan, maintaining contact with handlers even during recent blackouts in north India. Malhotra, along with Nauman Elahi, Devender Singh Dhillon, and Arman, are accused of sharing sensitive information about vital installations. Authorities are investigating Malhotra's role in shaping narratives and Arman's connection to Pakistani intelligence operatives.
title: Haryana 'spy ring': YouTuber Jyoti Malhotra, 3 others were in touch with Pak handlers

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Israel has recovered the official Syrian archive of spy Eli Cohen, executed in 1965, in a covert Mossad operation. The archive, containing 2,500 documents, photos, and personal items, was presented to Cohen's widow. Recovered materials include handwritten letters, forged passports, and the original death sentence, offering insights into Cohen's intelligence work and final days.
title: Israel recovers spy Eli Cohen's archive from Syria 60 years after he was hanged

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Sai Sudharsan credits Shubman Gill's direct feedback for his improved performance in the IPL, highlighted by his unbeaten 108 against Delhi Capitals. Together, their strong partnership, with Gill scoring 93 not out, guided Gujarat Titans to a dominant 10-wicket victory. Sudharsan's focus on calculated risks and understanding match situations has propelled him to the top of the Orange Cap race.
title: Sai Sudharsan spills the beans on Shubman Gill’s leadership style

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Suniel Shetty and Athiya Shetty celebrated KL Rahul's historic IPL feat, marking his centuries for three different franchises. Athiya expressed her support with a heartfelt tribute on social media. The couple, who married in January 2023, recently welcomed their daughter, Evaarah. Suniel Shetty proudly shared his admiration for Athiya's graceful transition into motherhood.
title: Suniel and Athiya Shetty shower love on KL Rahul for historic IPL feat

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Following a deadly terror attack in Jammu and Kashmir, the Indian Army launched Operation Sindoor on May 7, targeting nine terror-linked sites in Pakistan and PoK. The operation involved precision airstrikes and vigilance against Pakistani drones. In response to Pakistan's shelling and drone attempts, India broadened its strikes to include 11 airbases.
title: Watch: Army drops new video of Op Sindoor showing drone takedown, precision strikes

author: ROHIT KHANNA AND MOHAMMAD ASIF
description: Sherpa Palchen Tamang, accompanying Subrata Ghosh, recounted the harrowing Everest summit. Ghosh, weakened and disoriented near Hillary Step, refused to move despite Tamang's efforts. Exhausted and with dwindling oxygen, Tamang spent hours trying to move Ghosh, but was ultimately forced to descend alone, suffering hallucinations and frostbite during his own difficult return to camp.
title: 'Too tired': Bengal climber was abandoned in Everest ‘death zone’

author: TOI TRENDING DESK
description: Tragedy struck as the Mexican Navy's tall ship, Cuauhtémoc, collided with the Brooklyn Bridge, resulting in the deaths of two cadets and injuring 19 others. The ship, on a goodwill tour, lost power and drifted into the bridge, snapping its masts. América Yamilet Sánchez and Adal Jair Marcos were identified as the deceased. Investigations are underway by U.S.
title: Brooklyn Bridge accident kills two Mexican Navy cadets

author: TNN
description: Telangana and Andhra Pradesh police arrested two individuals, Sameer from Hyderabad and Siraj Ur Rehman from Vizianagaram. They were allegedly planning bomb blasts. Siraj procured bomb-making materials online. The duo intended to test explosives near Vizianagaram. Intelligence officials intervened after learning of the conspiracy. Interrogation revealed plans for a terrorist strike.
title: Cops foil terror bid; 2 held for plotting blasts, testing explosives

author: TANUJ LAKHINA
description: Shubman Gill's calm demeanour as a leader has propelled Gujarat Titans into the IPL 2025 playoffs and possibly a top-two finish. Backed by stellar batting form — second in the Orange Cap race — Gill leads by example with composed on-field conduct and relentless training. Shubman Gill has also emerged as a strong contender for future India Test captain. His unbeaten 93 against Delhi Capitals at the Arun Jaitley Stadium highlights his growing stature, making a strong case for his leadership in India’s post Rohit and Kohli era.
title: Shubman Gill strengthens case for India captaincy via Gujarat Titans

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Gujarat Titans, Royal Challengers Bengaluru, and Punjab Kings have secured their spots in the IPL 2025 playoffs. Gujarat Titans lead the table with 18 points, followed closely by RCB and PBKS with 17 each. The battle for the fourth playoff spot intensifies, with Mumbai Indians, Delhi Capitals, and Lucknow Super Giants vying for the final position.
title: EXPLAINED: MI, DC and LSG in brutal race for IPL 2025 playoffs

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Gujarat Titans secured their IPL 2025 playoff spot with a dominant 10-wicket victory over Delhi Capitals, fueled by Shubman Gill and Sai Sudharsan's unbeaten heroics. Sudharsan's 108 and Gill's 93 led a flawless chase of 200, showcasing their strong partnership and securing Gujarat's qualification with two matches to spare. Reflecting on his captaincy journey, Gill admitted to early struggles in the role but said he has since learned how to handle the pressure.
title: 'He is the reason we're here': Shubman Gill's emotional words

description: Brokerage firms have issued varied ratings on several companies. CLSA downgraded IndusInd Bank due to incorrectly recorded interest income. Jefferies maintains a buy rating on LIC Housing Finance, citing in-line net profit. Citigroup recommends buying PB Fintech, noting its better-than-expected net profit.

author: TNN
description: In Delhi, a disagreement regarding DJ services turned deadly. Bheem Sen, an 18-year-old, was fatally stabbed in Mahendra Park. The incident occurred after an argument with a juvenile about a DJ booking. Police arrested four individuals, all believed to be juveniles. They are being processed as Children in Conflict with Law. The investigation is ongoing to recover the weapon.

description: First responders in Hyderabad were deeply affected by the tragic scene of an elderly woman found dead, embracing four children in a fire-ravaged home. Despite attempts to rescue the Modi household residents, seven bodies were recovered, including the woman and children found huddled together. The rescuers described the unbearable sight of the victims, highlighting the devastating impact of the fire.
title: Hyderabad building fire: Woman found holding four children in final embrace

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Punjab Kings secured a playoff berth by defeating Rajasthan Royals. Nehal Wadhera and Shashank Singh scored half-centuries. Harpreet Brar took three wickets. author: SIDHARTHA
description: India is restricting ready-made garment imports from Bangladesh via land. This action is expected to raise logistics costs. Transit times will also increase. Apparel Export Promotion Council notes potential negative impacts. A significant portion of apparel imports enters India through land ports. The change will affect shipments through Petrapole land port. Ships will now sail to Kolkata and Mumbai.
title: Transit delays, higher costs: Bangladesh garment import curbs to hit buyers

author: TNN
description: The Uttar Pradesh Anti-Terrorist Squad (ATS) arrested Shehzad Wahab from Rampur, a suspected Pakistani spy involved in cross-border smuggling from Moradabad. He allegedly maintained direct contact with Inter-Services Intelligence (ISI) operatives, providing sensitive information related to India's internal security and facilitating financial transactions. Shehzad is also suspected of recruiting individuals for ISI and supplying Indian SIM cards to agents.
title: 'Shared info with ISI': UP ATS arrests man for spying for Pak, crossborder smuggling

author: TNN
description: Indian markets are poised to react to foreign fund activity, developments in the India-US trade deal, and the rupee-dollar exchange rate following Moody's US credit rating downgrade. Investors will also be watching quarterly earnings from major companies like ONGC and ITC. Strong participation from both FIIs and DIIs, coupled with global risk appetite, has fueled the recent market rally.
title: FPIs, India-US trade news to dictate Dalal-Street movement
